  <name>mrworldwide</name>
  <summary>Translate text elegantly</summary>
  <description>
    <p>The power of language in the palm of your hand</p>
    <p>
      Yet another translation app. This one uses DeepL as backend, and goes for the no-nonsense, simple and clean route.
      But i mostly just wanted to try out the UI, and needed something elementary OS to integrate with our elementary OS
    </p>
    <p>Features include:</p>
      <ul>
            <li>Nimble: Quick to setup: Paste your api key, whether DeepL Free or Pro, and here you go!</li>
            <li>Toggle the view to be either horizontal or vertical</li>
            <li>You can add context!</li>
            <li>Supported languages: All those available via DeepL API!</li>
            <li>Detect language: As expected of a translator!</li>
            <li>System language: No need to search for it in the list ;)</li>
            <li>TO COME (maybe): See your current usage!</li>
      </ul>
    <p>This is still under big development</p>
  </description>

